Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease cookie sheets. Cream together the butter and sugar. Add eggs, molasses and vanilla. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, cinnamon, and baking soda. Gradually add to the cream mixture. Stir in oatmeal, raisins, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes or until light brown.